derivation.yuyuan_name: late Middle English  (denoting any red deer stag in its second year, with straight antlers): from Anglo-Norman French broquet, diminutive of broque, variant of broche (see brooch) The current sense dates from the mid 19th cent

means.word_mean: 1. small South American deer with unbranched antlers
2. male red deer in its second year
